description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Band 5 Physiotherapist to join our inpatient Integrated therapy team.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The team is responsible for providing assessment and interventions to both in and outpatients in a range of settings, as well as hydrotherapy.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post will involve inpatient / outpatient care in the following areas&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Orthopaedics&lt;br /&gt;Neurology&lt;br /&gt;Respiratory&lt;br /&gt;Cardiothoracics&lt;br /&gt;Elderly&lt;br /&gt;Paediatric&lt;br /&gt;Stroke&lt;br /&gt;Community therapy&lt;br /&gt;Surgery&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate will gain experience of working within outpatients and inpatient acute services as well as community. They will take part in an inservice training programme, and will receive appropriate supervision.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The therapist will be part of the MDT, and work closely with the occupational therapists and other medical staff.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate must be able to demonstrate good communication skills, flexibility and a commitment to improving the patient’s experience. They will be required to show initiative and be able to organise and priorities their work effectively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Namemichelle.perham@btuh.nhs.ukAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bradley.Tiffin@btuh.nhs.uk (Therapy Lead - Stroke and Neuro Rehab)&lt;/p&gt;
